title: Grateful Dead Live at Saratoga Performing Arts Center on 1983-06-18
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi DR-2 > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > R8Brain > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 1644 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 03/2012
description:
Set 1

Bertha-> Jack Straw, Bird Song, Mexicali Blues-> Big River, Althea, Hell In A Bucket-> Deal

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Playin' In The Band Reprise-> Morning Dew, Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away-> Touch Of Gray, E:Don't Ease Me In-> E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: great new source This new source sounds the best to my ears. Jerry's guitar is louder, clearer, and more up front in this source than either beyer.huston.miller.105236 (which is great too) or set2.senn441.silberman.miller.103293.flac16 (digital, nice).  This source sounds closer but without extra crowd noise so that's great too. the cuts are patched up too! this ones the best! gotta love that lush, ethereal '83 energy. i can almost taste that acid everyone was on............
ditto from above awesome recording thanks bro
i agree with "natural" this sounds the best to me too; i just replaced the other i had (the huston/miller; it has no bass in the first set, and is less dimensional than this one.)

Agree better sound. I think this sound is better also.Maybe because its down lower in the bowl of the Pavillion. Has  full sound. man did it rian these first three shows.I am suprsied noone else hears the I can see clearly now.At the beginning of both Scarlet and Fire.
Good quality....but You might want to learn how to NOT have breaks between tunes.  It's actually quite simple and makes for better listening.

Major Probs with this source I was listening to this version of this show today.  There are major issues throughout the 2nd set.  Many portions of many songs were patched in a totally screwed up way so as to repeat significant chunks of those tunes (Scarlet for instance.  Also check the end of Deal).  If you have intuitive knowledge of the show from many listens, it is obvious and really irritating.  Sound is good, but once you tune in to the cuts/repeats it is not worth it.
The first set is just bad.  Althea is lackluster despite crown enthusiasm and Bucket is just a disaster.
Stick to the awesome 2nd set and another source.  

The first set really just

this recording is great please ignore the reviews here that mention gaps or repeating sections, they just are not true.   Andrew is a master at fixing up recordings, and this is no exception.  It might be the best sounding source from a venue that was hard to pull a good tape out of.

Deadhead225…WTF?’ I’m calling you out because you made one of the most grossly out touch and downright asinine comments in the review for this show. To wit: to suggest that the Althea was “lackluster” proves immediately that you have-at best-very questionable taste but I’m certain it goes deeper and so you’ll hear it from me. The Althea is one of the greatest versions ever played. The vocals despite Garcia being in a ragged state for his nightly singing duties, are absolutely riveting due to his delivery and due to the crowd very clearly egging him on. That’s all from me, just had to get it off my chest how wrong you were. This isn’t John Mayer singing these songs…Scarlet Fire from this show is so overwhelmingly jammed it may be the greatest ever. Another story altogether but I don’t think even someone as seemingly doomed to play in the proverbial Single A leagues of GD reviews for his entire career would be able to talk shit on that. Listen to both again, even if you get this years later similar to the time since you wrote that blasphemy, but remember, just because you realize how wrong you were upon reading this and perhaps consider going back to GD Reviewers Spring Training, being that wrong means you’ll never review in the Big Leagues if you know what I am saying ;) BLESS UP
